Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine in both serum and blood), marked proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low blood glucose. Urine is cloudy, brown, and has abnormal odor, but no evidence of infection (negative nitrite/leukocytes). Findings suggest possible acute or chronic kidney disease with nephrotic-range proteinuria and possible tubular dysfunction. Further clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are recommended.
